JAPANESE ENCEPHALITIS - NEPAL (03)
**********************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.healthnet.org/programs/promed.html>
See Also
Japanese encephalitis - Nepal 980827232947
Japanese encephalitis - Nepal (02) 980828224029
Date: 29 Aug 98 09:57:29 +0000
From: Dr. D. D. Joshi <dd_joshi@npl.healthnet.org>
Via: HNET Nepal Gateway - Kathmandu, NEPAL

In mid-western Nepal at Bheri Zonal Hospital Nepalganj till to date a total
of 73 cases have been admitted and recorded so far out of which 12 died of
JE, 41 patients have recovered after treatment, while 20 patients are still
under treatment in the hospital. Every day, 7-8 new JE patients are getting
into hospital from Banke, Dang, Berdia, Kailali, Dailekh, Bajura and also
from Border Indian districts of India.
Last year 1997 - total JE cases admitted and reported in Bheri Zonal
Hospital were 823 out of which 123 died.
This report of JE outbreaks are also being published regularly in most
common government as well as in Private local News papers like Gorkha
Patra, Rising Nepal, Kantipur, and Kathmandu Post.
--
Dr. D. D. Joshi, Director
National Zoonoses and Food Hygiene Research Centre
